1. Write query to find Nth highest salary

Example: 3rd highest salary

SELECT DISTINCT salary
FROM employees
ORDER BY salary DESC
LIMIT 1 OFFSET 2;


2. Remove duplicate records

Assume table employees(emp_id, emp_name, salary).

DELETE e1
FROM employees e1
JOIN employees e2
ON e1.emp_name = e2.emp_name
AND e1.emp_id > e2.emp_id;


3. Find records common in two tables

Suppose tables table1(id, name) and table2(id, name).

SELECT *
FROM table1
INTERSECT
SELECT *
FROM table2;

If INTERSECT is not supported (MySQL):

SELECT t1.*
FROM table1 t1
JOIN table2 t2
ON t1.id = t2.id;


4. Find employees hired in last 6 months

Assume table employees(emp_id, emp_name, hire_date).

SELECT *
FROM employees
WHERE hire_date >= DATE_SUB(CURDATE(), INTERVAL 6 MONTH);


5. Find continuous duplicate values

Assume table logs(id, value).

SELECT DISTINCT l1.value
FROM logs l1
JOIN logs l2
ON l1.id + 1 = l2.id
AND l1.value = l2.value;

These are common advanced SQL interview and practical queries.
